---
description: Docs + Bruno collection hygiene (keep docs aligned with code)
globs: "**/*.{md,bru,json}"
alwaysApply: false
---

## Docs

- Keep documentation aligned with implementation (avoid “drift”).
- When documenting env vars or endpoints, mirror the actual names/paths used in `src/`.
- If docs describe behavior that differs from code, prefer updating docs to match the code unless the change request says otherwise.

## Bruno collections (`bruno-collection/`)

- Keep request names and foldering consistent with the existing collection structure.
- Prefer stable endpoint paths that match `src/routes/` mounting (e.g. `/api/v1/...`).
